---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const steamLink = 'https://store.steampowered.com/app/4642060/InVein/';
---
<Layout
  title="Malik Danab - InVein"
  description="InVein is a psychological horror game on Steam. Malik Danab built its sound systems, radio system, and gamma implementation in Unreal Engine."
  active="projects"
  image="/images/cover-invein.webp"
>
  <main class="page-modules">
    <h1 class="page-title">InVein</h1>
    <p class="page-subtitle">Gameplay &amp; Sound Programmer &middot; Unreal Engine 5 &middot; Released on Steam</p>
    <div class="image-block logo">
      <a href={steamLink} target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        <img src="/images/invein-1.webp" alt="InVein" width="999" height="639" />
      </a>
    </div>
    <div class="module-columns">
      <div class="text-block">
        <div>
          <a href={steamLink} target="_blank" rel="noopener">InVein</a> is a psychological horror
          game where you play as a patient exploring a disturbing, ever-changing hospital, relying
          on a limited IV supply to stay alive. As you move through rooms, solve puzzles, and
          uncover unsettling clues, reality begins to break down, and the staff becomes
          something far more dangerous.
        </div>
        <div>Engine &amp; Tools: Unreal Engine 5, Perforce</div>
      </div>
      <div class="video-block">
        <div class="video-frame">
          <iframe
            src="https://www-ccv.adobe.io/v1/player/ccv/57-qcx58jFp/embed?bgcolor=%23191919&lazyLoading=true&api_key=BehancePro2View"
            title="InVein gameplay video"
            loading="lazy"
            allowfullscreen
          ></iframe>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="text-block">
      <h2 class="title">What I Built</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="text-block">
      <h3 class="sub-title">Radio &amp; Dynamic Sound System</h3>
      <div>
        I built and integrated the radio and the dynamic sound system behind the game's
        atmosphere. Instead of playing sounds on fixed triggers, the system reacts to what's
        happening around the player. Audio carries most of the pacing in a horror game, so this
        system does a lot of the scare work.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="text-block">
      <h3 class="sub-title">Gamma Correction &amp; Rendering Stability</h3>
      <div>
        I programmed the gamma correction and rendering stability features that keep the game's
        carefully-tuned darkness readable and consistent across different monitors and hardware
        setups. That matters a lot in a game where almost everything happens in low light.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="text-block">
      <h3 class="sub-title">Debugging the Reality Shifts</h3>
      <div>
        The hospital rearranges itself around the player. I spent a lot of time debugging these
        reality-shifting sequences, tracking down performance and state-sync issues in some of
        the hardest parts of the game to get right.
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
